Program: Outlook
Title: Surgeon in the Chechnya Conflict
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03kbsff
Last Broadcast Date: Not available
A surgeon who paid a high price for treating anyone who needed help in the war in Chechnya. Also, the work of BEN, the Bicycle Empowerment Network, founded by Michael Linke, which recycles old bicycles in Namibia. How victims of the Mumbai train bombings are coping with their injuries. Finally the peace movement which uses silence to help women find their voice. Show less